-- Power Grid Plans to Raise 15 Billion Rupees Selling Bonds Due in 15 Years
-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 2010-10-20T10:39:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/power-grid-plans-to-raise-15-billion-rupees-selling-bonds-due-in-15-years.html
Power Grid Corp. of India Ltd.  sold
15 billion rupees ($338 million) of 15-year, 8.84 percent bonds,
according to three people with knowledge of the matter, who
asked not to be identified because the information is private.  The state-run company told bidders on Oct. 11 that it would
pay a maximum coupon of 8.72 percent the bonds, people familiar
with the transaction said at the time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Anurag Joshi  in Mumbai 
